{
  "stem": "188.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, this was prior to-- well, the Germans were in Holland, but they were not on the farm there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was just-- that was prior to that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was just briefly one night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was a big treat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I must have been 11 or 12, probably 12, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] going on 100.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Canadian Army came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had a radio in our hiding place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was always tuned to the BBC.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we were somewhat up to date as to how far the Allies were.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] My father was out of the house when the first tank started rolling, and he almost got killed because they were still shooting at each other.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Seeing the Canadians come in, it-- I was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I comprehended it, but I didn't quite believe it, that this was really, yes, I think we've survived it.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And there was still-- there was-- there was fear.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was still-- on the day that we were liberated in '45, that evening, we were allowed to come downstairs and be with the whole family.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the door opened, and here was a young German soldier who had deserted, with a machine gun, facing us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And both my father and Bernard Roerink somehow talked him into putting his weapon down and subduing him.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they took him host-- they took him prisoner.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "A prisoner.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And-- but that we didn't get killed that last minute, to me, that's a miracle.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He just wanted to be safe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think he was so panic-stricken that if it had meant mowing down a room full of people, he would have.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were able to reason with him.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
